  "body": "I just realized one `get_beacon_proposer_index` call could be saved by passing in `block` as the argument to `process_randao`:\r\n```python\r\ndef process_block(state: BeaconState, block: BeaconBlock) -> None:\r\n    ...\r\n    process_randao(state, block)\r\n   ...\r\n\r\ndef process_randao(state: BeaconState, block: BeaconBlock) -> None:\r\n   ...\r\n    # Verify RANDAO reveal\r\n    # proposer = state.validators[get_beacon_proposer_index(state)]\r\n    proposer = block.proposer_index\r\n```\r\n\r\nGiven we are late in the spec game, I don't have a strong desire to modify the spec to reflect such optimization and readability improvement. I just wanted to point this out because the client code could still use this change for lesser lines and/or minor speed improvement (e.g. one less look up)\r\n",
