    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think we considered this a while back and decided that because `proposer_index` is validated in `process_block_header` that we can just safely derive it in `process_randao` and not modify the function signature.\r\n\r\nI think we were aiming to reduce the amount of changes and new testing when `proposer_index` was added to `BeaconBlock`, and using the derivation from the block header satisfied that.\r\n\r\nAgree that as long as `assert block.proposer_index == get_beacon_proposer_index(state)` from `process_block_header` has passed, then both ways of deriving the `proposer_index` are safe",
